result.execSummary:
The defendant Nicholas A. Craig was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).
  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).
  • Maintain Drug Trafficking Place [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.42(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Conditions for Counts 3, 4, and 5:  Pay costs.  Attend, pay for, and successfully complete any educational and/or counseling that's ordered by the agent.  Follow all rules and regulations of the agent.  Submit to AODA and follow through with all recommendations.

Additionally, for Count 3, Defendant is to pay a fine and costs ($3000 base fine plus costs).  If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due. All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Defendant Nicholas A. Craig in court with attorney Timothy Luke Angel. Prosecuting Atty Jennifer M. Harper appeared for State of Wisconsin.  Counsel inform the Court that they've reached an agreement for resolution in 14CF81 and 14CF82.  Per Atty. Angel, Def will be pleading to Counts 1, 2, and 3 of 14CF82 for dismissal/read-in of 14CF81 and dismissal/read-in of counts 4 and 5 in 14CF82.  DA Harper states the offer was for disposition on Counts 4 and 5 of 14CF82 and Count 1 of 14CF81.  Court adjourns this matter to allow the parties to further negotiate/determine the offer.

Matter recalled.  DA recites the agreement, calling for def's pleads to counts 3, 4, and 5 of 14CF82.  DA has offered amendments so that all three charges are for maintaining drug house per 961.42(1); Count 5 has a party-to-the-crime modifier but counts 3 and 4, once amended, will not.  Amendments allowed.  Def pleads no contest to those three counts.  Finding of guilty. 

Each count - sentence withheld for probation of 5 years.  On Count 3, there will be a condition that def pay $3000 fine plus costs; that's a condition of probation.  On all counts, condition will be attend, pay for, and successfully complete any education/counseling ordered by agent; follow all rules/regs of agent; aoda/follow through.

Firearms and other felony admonishments provided.

Def states he's provided DNA sample in the past.

Court orders dismissal/read-in of 14CF81 and the same for counts 1 and 2 of 14CF82.
